snippet.textDisplay:
Please read this as I want to share this with you.

I can't believe it, nintendo you just won yourself. My childhood game to which I held many memories with just got remade. Guys, do you know how much I love this game and what kind of moments I shared with?

Ahaha, I still wont forget the day when my dad got me this. So, as I was in currys I saw a huge basket of pokemon mystery dungeon red in there so I begged my dad to please get me this and after a long convincing, which to no end... my dad bought me it :D only on one condition that I may play this on my birthday also as my dad got 2 of these games for me and my siblings but my other siblings didnt have one because my dad was in a hurry so he was like, play it when your birthday day comes and I was like I want to play it now so my dad told me to play it underneath your bed ahahah so yeah, I was there opened the game and the first time I played it was underneath my bed.

I played the game countless times and it got restarted, so many times that I lost count but every time I played it I was so eager to finish it off and I remember the days when I went to school and the lessons...it was so boring that when I used think about playing Pokemon Mystery Dungeon Red, it gave like a burst of happiness. Man, I totally recommend all of you newcomers playing this and now the main game that needs to be remade is Pokemon Mystrey Dungeon Explorer of Sky.

snippet.textDisplay: Am I the only one that thinks Urshifu Rapid Strike Style should have been Psychic-Fighting? Urshifu Single Strike Style is Dark-Fighting type because it uses it’s rage to release a full power strike. And Psychic types are usually calm (this is a reference to the Pokemon move Calm Mind) so it would make sense. Plus, we don’t have much Psychic-Fighting types, the only ones I can think of off the top of my head is Medicham and Mega Mewtwo X.
